# .gitleaksignore — suppress known false-positive Gitleaks findings
#
# Format: <commit-sha>:<rule-id>
#
# To identify findings: look at the gitleaks output in the "Secret Scan (Gitleaks)"
# check run, note the commit SHA and rule ID, then add them here.
#
# Terraform template placeholders (infra/terraform/templates/*.tpl) use
# ${variable} syntax that can trigger generic-api-key or similar rules.
# These are NOT real secrets; they are filled in by Terraform at apply time.
